Beef and mutton paomo.

34
00:02:58,390 --> 00:02:59,790
Spicy garlic lamb blood.

35
00:03:00,310 --> 00:03:01,590
You're weak, aren't you?

36
00:03:01,590 --> 00:03:02,840
Just a couple of hits

37
00:03:03,120 --> 00:03:04,450
got you in a wheelchair.

38
00:03:04,960 --> 00:03:05,490
Get lost.

39
00:03:06,580 --> 00:03:08,800
Shut your mouth if you can't talk nicely.

40
00:03:08,800 --> 00:03:10,630
Let that car hit you and see how you feel.

41
00:03:10,630 --> 00:03:12,150
-Yeah.
-I'm doing fine.

42
00:03:12,150 --> 00:03:13,150
The mutton soup is ready.

43
00:03:13,150 --> 00:03:14,120
Drink a few bowls,

44
00:03:14,120 --> 00:03:15,180
and you'll be fine.

45
00:03:15,470 --> 00:03:17,000
Once our relics protection
team is established,

46
00:03:17,000 --> 00:03:18,150
we'll definitely avenge you.

47
00:03:18,150 --> 00:03:20,150
What team are you talking about now?

48
00:03:20,150 --> 00:03:21,170
We don't even patrol anymore.

49
00:03:21,170 --> 00:03:23,800
Now we have a monitoring room.

50
00:03:23,910 --> 00:03:24,520
Come on.

51
00:03:24,520 --> 00:03:25,120
Lift it up a bit.

52
00:03:25,120 --> 00:03:26,850
Lift it up. Three, two, one, go.

53
00:03:27,470 --> 00:03:28,750
Careful.

54
00:03:29,150 --> 00:03:30,950
Coming. The mutton soup is here.

55
00:03:35,030 --> 00:03:36,360
Come on, I'm using the computer.

56
00:03:36,360 --> 00:03:37,960
Do you even know how?

57
00:03:38,870 --> 00:03:40,470
You don't know anything, and still—

58
00:03:40,470 --> 00:03:42,000
Get me a bowl of mutton soup.

59
00:03:42,079 --> 00:03:43,940
I've been stewing it all morning.

60
00:03:43,960 --> 00:03:45,400
Start eating, come on.

61
00:03:45,630 --> 00:03:46,840
You serve the soup to everyone.

62
00:03:46,840 --> 00:03:48,120
I'll eat a bun.

63
00:03:48,280 --> 00:03:48,680
Have a bun.

64
00:03:48,680 --> 00:03:49,150
Come on.

65
00:03:50,560 --> 00:03:51,420
This is so good.

66
00:03:51,560 --> 00:03:52,240
So good.

67
00:03:52,310 --> 00:03:53,570
I'd like another bowl.

68
00:03:57,960 --> 00:03:59,020
Here, mutton soup.

69
00:03:59,360 --> 00:04:00,820
Come on, drink it quickly.

70
00:04:00,910 --> 00:04:02,040
It'll get cold soon.

71
00:04:05,800 --> 00:04:06,130
Here.

72
00:04:06,400 --> 00:04:06,960
It's yours.

73
00:04:06,960 --> 00:04:07,690
You drink it.

74
00:04:07,910 --> 00:04:08,590
I won't.

75
00:04:08,710 --> 00:04:09,520
Have a seat.

76
00:04:09,630 --> 00:04:10,150
Sit down.

77
00:04:10,150 --> 00:04:11,310
Just sit.

78
00:04:23,190 --> 00:04:24,480
You... Help yourself.

79
00:04:26,120 --> 00:04:28,360
Luo Qing said

80
00:04:29,360 --> 00:04:31,510
the sounding stone

81
00:04:32,470 --> 00:04:33,560
and these

82
00:04:34,800 --> 00:04:35,680
chime bells

83
00:04:37,320 --> 00:04:40,470
should have come from

84
00:04:42,870 --> 00:04:43,950
this pit.

85
00:04:45,070 --> 00:04:47,330
And this matches the lotus candlestick.

86
00:04:47,560 --> 00:04:49,620
The gilt lotus leaf we found in the pit

87
00:04:49,800 --> 00:04:51,120
must have been dropped

88
00:04:51,120 --> 00:04:52,520
when they were taking it.

89
00:04:52,630 --> 00:04:53,030
Right.

90
00:04:59,600 --> 00:05:00,750
This is

91
00:05:02,270 --> 00:05:03,270
an official seal.

92
00:05:04,270 --> 00:05:05,950
We think so.

93
00:05:07,720 --> 00:05:08,800
Did the tomb raider

94
00:05:09,720 --> 00:05:10,480
say

95
00:05:11,510 --> 00:05:12,170
there's any

96
00:05:14,190 --> 00:05:15,120
inscriptions?

97
00:05:15,240 --> 00:05:15,800
Yes.

98
00:05:16,510 --> 00:05:17,830
That's why I'm here.

99
00:05:19,040 --> 00:05:20,770
The tomb raider couldn't recognize them.

100
00:05:20,770 --> 00:05:21,740
I've heard

101
00:05:22,160 --> 00:05:26,020
bronze artifacts are more valuable
the more inscriptions they have.

102
00:05:26,160 --> 00:05:27,020
I was thinking,

103
00:05:27,560 --> 00:05:30,200
if you could use this to

104
00:05:30,510 --> 00:05:32,470
determine whose tomb it is,

105
00:05:32,630 --> 00:05:35,630
it might be even more
valuable than solving this case.

106
00:05:39,000 --> 00:05:39,740
Professional.

107
00:05:39,740 --> 00:05:40,510
I'm not that good.

108
00:05:40,510 --> 00:05:42,110
Just learning from you guys.

109
00:05:48,240 --> 00:05:49,800
I've discussed it with Guo.

110
00:05:50,190 --> 00:05:52,600
This is an official seal
based on its style.

111
00:05:53,070 --> 00:05:54,430
If it was found in the outer burial pit,

112
00:05:54,430 --> 00:05:56,490
it must be some sort of official seal.

113
00:06:11,070 --> 00:06:12,240
There's more food.

114
00:06:12,240 --> 00:06:13,070
Eat up.

115
00:06:14,680 --> 00:06:16,810
If you like spicy food, add some chili.

116
00:06:19,600 --> 00:06:20,600
Sit down.

117
00:06:20,630 --> 00:06:21,750
Eat quickly.

118
00:06:46,040 --> 00:06:49,800
It's basically this type of

119
00:06:51,360 --> 00:06:52,159
combination.

120
00:06:53,800 --> 00:06:54,360
Alright.

121
00:06:54,630 --> 00:06:55,750
Can I take it back

122
00:06:56,040 --> 00:06:57,680
and let the tomb raider identify it?

123
00:06:57,680 --> 00:06:58,120
Okay.

124
00:06:58,560 --> 00:07:00,160
I'll get back to you after that.

125
00:07:00,160 --> 00:07:00,690
Alright.

126
00:07:03,270 --> 00:07:06,040
Can it be retrieved?

127
00:07:07,720 --> 00:07:08,720
Hard to say.

128
00:07:10,070 --> 00:07:11,130
It's been too long.

129
00:07:12,600 --> 00:07:15,460
We can't rule out that
it's passed through customs.

130
00:07:15,600 --> 00:07:17,270
If it's gone overseas,

131
00:07:17,720 --> 00:07:18,800
finding it would be

132
00:07:19,430 --> 00:07:21,630
like looking for a needle in a haystack.

133
00:07:22,800 --> 00:07:23,460
Captain Qi,

134
00:07:23,830 --> 00:07:26,240
how can we find it
with just these few drawings?

135
00:07:26,240 --> 00:07:27,190
In a while,

136
00:07:27,190 --> 00:07:29,430
Qinchuan is going to launch

137
00:07:29,920 --> 00:07:33,800
a platform for publishing information
on stolen Chinese cultural relics,

138
00:07:33,800 --> 00:07:38,270
by the Ministry of Public Security
and the National Cultural Heritage Administration,

139
00:07:38,270 --> 00:07:41,270
commissioned to the provincial department.

140
00:07:41,830 --> 00:07:44,800
I heard it has info on
all stolen cultural relics

141
00:07:44,800 --> 00:07:47,800
since the founding of
the People's Republic of China.

142
00:07:48,430 --> 00:07:50,510
So, if it's really the case,

143
00:07:50,750 --> 00:07:54,190
then people worldwide can report it

144
00:07:54,680 --> 00:07:55,880
as soon as they see it.

145
00:07:56,310 --> 00:07:57,310
So I was thinking,

146
00:07:57,480 --> 00:07:59,210
we could upload these patterns

147
00:07:59,390 --> 00:08:00,320
and give it a try.

148
00:08:01,000 --> 00:08:01,330
Okay.

149
00:08:04,240 --> 00:08:05,680
Many hands make...

150
00:08:07,920 --> 00:08:08,580
light work.

151
00:08:09,680 --> 00:08:10,280
Which one?

152
00:08:19,680 --> 00:08:20,480
The one above.

153
00:08:20,870 --> 00:08:21,400
This one?

154
00:08:24,630 --> 00:08:25,630
Exactly the same?

155
00:08:27,680 --> 00:08:29,410
I only glanced at it a few times.

156
00:08:29,950 --> 00:08:31,550
I can't remember it clearly.

157
00:08:32,240 --> 00:08:34,240
But this one looks the most similar.

158
00:08:58,840 --> 00:08:59,480
Guo.

159
00:09:02,150 --> 00:09:02,600
You're

160
00:09:03,840 --> 00:09:04,630
packing up

161
00:09:05,510 --> 00:09:06,360
to go where?

162
00:09:07,270 --> 00:09:08,240
Going home.

163
00:09:08,630 --> 00:09:09,910
Haven't been back in a while.

164
00:09:09,910 --> 00:09:12,510
My wife's going to show me
the three-piece set.

165
00:09:13,480 --> 00:09:15,200
What's the three-piece set?

166
00:09:19,960 --> 00:09:20,510
"Hello."

167
00:09:21,320 --> 00:09:22,050
"Excuse me."

168
00:09:22,870 --> 00:09:24,080
"Sorry for the trouble."

169
00:09:24,080 --> 00:09:25,790
It's more distant than when we first met.

170
00:09:25,790 --> 00:09:26,910
If I don't go back now,

171
00:09:26,910 --> 00:09:28,910
we'll become the most familiar strangers.

172
00:09:28,910 --> 00:09:30,720
But you're getting there too.

173
00:09:30,740 --> 00:09:31,620
Don't envy me.

174
00:09:34,630 --> 00:09:35,080
But

175
00:09:37,840 --> 00:09:38,910
if you're leaving,

176
00:09:40,080 --> 00:09:41,720
what about me?

177
00:09:42,720 --> 00:09:43,630
I even...

178
00:09:58,840 --> 00:10:00,680
I've prepared everything for you.

179
00:10:00,680 --> 00:10:02,910
Besides, there's still Luo Qing, right?

180
00:10:02,910 --> 00:10:03,360
That girl

181
00:10:03,360 --> 00:10:05,160
has expressed herself clearly.

182
00:10:05,190 --> 00:10:06,670
You should hurry up and get this fire

183
00:10:06,670 --> 00:10:07,670
burning quickly.

184
00:10:10,790 --> 00:10:12,390
I'll leave this place to you.

185
00:10:12,630 --> 00:10:13,270
The rest

186
00:10:14,550 --> 00:10:15,240
is up to you.

187
00:10:23,630 --> 00:10:24,230
Good luck.

188
00:10:41,510 --> 00:10:42,080
Fang.

189
00:10:42,910 --> 00:10:44,770
The weather is really nice today.

190
00:10:46,600 --> 00:10:47,550
It's very nice.

191
00:10:48,630 --> 00:10:49,090
Well...

192
00:10:51,440 --> 00:10:51,910
Fang,

193
00:10:52,600 --> 00:10:53,730
I'll leave you here.

194
00:10:56,390 --> 00:10:56,910
Okay.

195
00:10:58,960 --> 00:11:00,270
You can enjoy some sunshine.

196
00:11:00,270 --> 00:11:00,750
Alright.

197
00:11:00,750 --> 00:11:01,600
I have something to do.

198
00:11:01,600 --> 00:11:01,960
Okay.

199
00:11:02,360 --> 00:11:03,510
Thank you.

200
00:11:03,840 --> 00:11:04,370
Alright.

201
00:12:13,790 --> 00:12:15,050
You're quite capable.

202
00:12:15,360 --> 00:12:17,620
You managed to move here all by yourself.

203
00:12:20,630 --> 00:12:21,760
Where are you going?

204
00:12:22,400 --> 00:12:23,360
Going home.

205
00:12:25,320 --> 00:12:26,720
You have the determination
to move back home,

206
00:12:26,720 --> 00:12:28,250
but not the resolve to stay?

207
00:12:29,150 --> 00:12:29,810
I don't want

208
00:12:30,740 --> 00:12:31,580
to be a burden.

209
00:12:43,200 --> 00:12:46,060
The archaeological team
doesn't keep idle people.

210
00:12:46,630 --> 00:12:47,600
Even if you're a burden,

211
00:12:47,600 --> 00:12:49,060
you're still a useful one.

212
00:12:51,270 --> 00:12:53,400
Right now, you're good for something.

213
00:12:56,550 --> 00:12:57,390
Tell me.

214
00:12:59,270 --> 00:13:00,150
Do you remember

215
00:13:00,750 --> 00:13:02,200
where did the claim that
Zi Mausoleum is on Phoenix Mountain

216
00:13:02,200 --> 00:13:03,460
originally come from?

217
00:13:08,550 --> 00:13:10,360
From Luo Tianxiang's

218
00:13:12,000 --> 00:13:13,510
Classified Records of Chang'an.

219
00:13:13,510 --> 00:13:13,870
Yes.

220
00:13:14,480 --> 00:13:16,870
Zi Mausoleum is 20 km east
of Jingzhao Tonghua Gate,

221
00:13:16,870 --> 00:13:19,270
at the foot of Phoenix Mountain
north of Bailu Plain.

222
00:13:19,270 --> 00:13:21,000
There's a paragraph to follow.

223
00:13:21,200 --> 00:13:22,960
In the autumn of the Xinmao year,

224
00:13:22,960 --> 00:13:24,960
the Zishui River burst open
the outer gate of Zi Mausoleum,

225
00:13:24,960 --> 00:13:27,090
washing out more than 500 stone slabs.

226
00:13:30,600 --> 00:13:32,060
What are you trying to say?

227
00:13:32,670 --> 00:13:33,840
If we take it literally,

228
00:13:33,840 --> 00:13:34,600
this "outer gate"

229
00:13:34,600 --> 00:13:37,270
should refer to the outer gate
of Zi Mausoleum's tomb passage.

230
00:13:37,270 --> 00:13:39,320
In other words, during the Zhiyuan era,

231
00:13:39,320 --> 00:13:42,390
the Zishui River burst open
this tomb passage's outer gate.

232
00:13:42,390 --> 00:13:44,360
I don't know what
"washing out stone slabs" means,

233
00:13:44,360 --> 00:13:45,960
but I guess this is

234
00:13:46,000 --> 00:13:47,150
Luo Tianxiang's basis

235
00:13:47,150 --> 00:13:49,320
for determining that Zi Mausoleum
is on Phoenix Mountain.

236
00:13:49,320 --> 00:13:51,200
And it's described in great detail.

237
00:13:51,200 --> 00:13:53,270
But if we can't explain it properly,

238
00:13:53,720 --> 00:13:55,320
this statement can't stand,

239
00:13:55,790 --> 00:13:57,250
and no one will believe it.

240
00:13:58,120 --> 00:14:00,030
The institute thinks the same way.

241
00:14:00,030 --> 00:14:01,840
So they sent
a geophysical prospecting company

242
00:14:01,840 --> 00:14:03,360
to use technological means

243
00:14:03,360 --> 00:14:05,240
to obtain potential information about

244
00:14:05,240 --> 00:14:08,080
remains, artifacts, and relics
on Phoenix Mountain.

245
00:14:08,080 --> 00:14:10,550
After the second exploration,
they'll move on to the third.

246
00:14:10,550 --> 00:14:14,790
Can any high-tech method
compare to a shovel?

247
00:14:15,000 --> 00:14:15,750
Indeed.

248
00:14:16,320 --> 00:14:18,250
The final results are all the same.

249
00:14:18,670 --> 00:14:20,120
But to overturn

250
00:14:20,120 --> 00:14:21,510
a thousand years of recorded history

251
00:14:21,510 --> 00:14:22,600
is not so easy.

252
00:14:23,750 --> 00:14:25,720
So the most important thing right now

253
00:14:25,720 --> 00:14:28,270
is to figure out
the Classified Records of Chang'an.

254
00:14:28,270 --> 00:14:30,270
Only then can we convince everyone.

255
00:14:32,360 --> 00:14:34,030
What can I do?

256
00:14:34,600 --> 00:14:36,860
All my people are up on Phoenix Mountain.

257
00:14:36,960 --> 00:14:38,690
I can't spare anyone to do this.

258
00:14:39,390 --> 00:14:40,650
So I have to rely on you.

259
00:14:41,240 --> 00:14:43,120
What can I do in this condition?

260
00:14:43,440 --> 00:14:44,510
You're Fang Kun.

261
00:14:45,000 --> 00:14:46,000
You're asking me?

262
00:14:46,650 --> 00:14:48,850
Didn't you used to have plenty of ideas?

263
00:14:49,550 --> 00:14:51,840
Like when you stopped Ma Chaoyue
from filling the looting pit.

264
00:14:51,840 --> 00:14:53,360
Where did that spirit go?

265
00:14:55,510 --> 00:14:56,040
Alright.

266
00:14:57,080 --> 00:14:57,840
I can see that.

267
00:14:57,840 --> 00:14:58,960
You have a bunch of excuses.

268
00:14:58,960 --> 00:15:00,000
Then I have no choice.

269
00:15:00,000 --> 00:15:01,720
I can't force you with a knife.

270
00:15:02,480 --> 00:15:03,080
Right?

271
00:15:03,550 --> 00:15:06,010
So we'll just keep
postponing this project.

272
00:15:06,080 --> 00:15:08,280
I have no idea how long it'll be delayed.

273
00:15:08,740 --> 00:15:10,910
When I go to see Mr. Zan later,

274
00:15:11,600 --> 00:15:13,000
I'll bring him a message,

275
00:15:13,680 --> 00:15:16,770
saying "Your prized disciple, Fang Kun,

276
00:15:17,150 --> 00:15:19,860
has already left our archaeological team

277
00:15:20,350 --> 00:15:22,400
due to his temporary leg problem.

278
00:15:23,150 --> 00:15:24,960
And he's left the mess from years ago

279
00:15:24,960 --> 00:15:27,120
to poor me and Guo Shilin.

280
00:15:27,600 --> 00:15:30,200
I've put aside the Lv Family Tomb

281
00:15:30,550 --> 00:15:31,870
to come here and help.

282
00:15:33,200 --> 00:15:34,730
He can't blame me for that."

283
00:15:35,810 --> 00:15:36,600
You're coercing me.

284
00:15:36,600 --> 00:15:38,170
Yes, I am.

285
00:15:39,000 --> 00:15:40,260
Not just using Mr. Zan,

286
00:15:40,320 --> 00:15:42,790
